Hi folks.

Finally got Leopard installed this evening.  Straight upgrade install,
must've taken around 70 - 80 minutes or so.  Fantastic so far and I'd
guess a slight performance improvement.  Very happy that features like
Cover Flow work as well (FAST) on this old G4 PowerMac as they did on
the preview videos.

Now, the Firewall looks entirely different to what I was used to in Tiger.

It was set to 'Allow all incoming connections'.  Is 'Block all incoming
connections' much the same as having the firewall turned on in 10.4?
'Set access for specific services and applications' looks rather similar
to what Little Snitch does.

Thoughts?

Cheers,
Andy.
