I have always upgraded to the 10.N.0 versions and never noticed any
problems whatsoever.  So I never really took much notice of those who said
that they wait for the 10.N.1 versions before upgrading.  However, with
Leopard, there have been enough things that really show that it was rushed
to meet the deadline.  So in this case, I would recommend waiting for
10.5.1 unless you have a pressing need for Leopard features.

I should say that all of my update installs went well overall, but there
still are things that have gotten to me.   For example, the new Address
Book seems to have merged all of  my &quot;No Name&quot; entries into one.

I seem to be the only person who doesn't mind stacks, but that seems to be
because prior to Stacks, I never kept folders in the Dock (I did put some
in Finder's sidebar.)  I also don't know what a &quot;spring loaded&quot; folder is
supposed to be anyway.

Cheers,

